prompt.en:
**Calculator**
Create all necessary classes so that the execution of the provided code displays the specified results. A base abstract class for operations is required, from which Adunare, Scadere, Inmultire, and Impartire are derived. The Calculator class must manage these operations using polymorphism.

**Constraints:**
- No STL templates allowed (e.g., map, unordered_map, etc.)
- operator+= adds an operation ONLY IF IT DOES NOT ALREADY EXIST in the calculator

**Observations:**
- Read the next page for grading criteria

**main():**
```cpp
int main()
{
    Calculator c;
    c += new Adunare();
    c += new Scadere();
    c += new Adunare(); // NU se mai adauga inca o operatie de adunare
    c += new Inmultire();
    c += new Impartire();
    std::cout << "Numar operatii suportate: " << (int)c << std::endl;
    c.Compute(20, 10);
    if (c["Scadere"])
        std::cout << "Operatia de scadere este suportata de calculator" << std::endl;
    c -= "Scadere";
    c -= "Impartire";
    c.Compute(15, 6);
    std::cout << "Numar operatii suportate: " << (int)c << std::endl;
}
```

**Expected output:**
```
Numar operatii suportate: 4
Adunare(20,10) = 30
Scadere(20,10) = 10
Inmultire(20,10) = 200
Impartire(20,10) = 2
Operatia de scadere este suportata de calculator
Adunare(15,6) = 21
Inmultire(15,6) = 90
Numar operatii suportate: 2
```

